{
  "texts": [
    "EVs are modeled as controlled loads whose demand E EV k can be modulated by the RL agents to maintain grid stability during congested periods.",
    "D. MEASUREMENT LAYER AND STATE ACQUISITIONEach bus is assumed to have a PMU-like sensing layer capable of reporting:s k = V k, θ k, P L,k, Q L,k, S solar k, S wind k, SOC k, E EV k, f k ⊤.",
    "(40) These measurements form the state vector used by all controllers.",
    "Sensor update rates are 1 second, matching real-time distribution-level monitoring systems.",
    "Measurement noise is modeled as:v k ∼ N (0, σ 2 v),(41)with σ 2 v chosen to represent typical PMU and micro-PMU noise characteristics."
  ]
}